timing_spatial_derate_chip_size(25.10)  timing_spatial_derate_chip_size(25.10)

Name
       timing_spatial_derate_chip_size

Syntax
       timing_spatial_derate_chip_size <value_in_microns>

       Default: 1e+30

       Allows you to define the chip size.

       The  chip  size is the diagonal length of a rectangle that is formed by
       the chip's length and width. You can obtain the  diagonal  distance  by
       calculating  the square-root of the Length2 + Width2. The diagonal dis-
       tance should always be specified in units of microns.

       The chip size can be picked in the following ways (in order of  highest
       to lowest precedence):

              * When set to a value other than 1e+30, the specified value will
                have the highest precedence.

              * If  the  physical floorplan information is available, the chip
                size will be derived automatically from the floorplan.

              * If the SPEF parasitic files containing the coordinate informa-
                tion are loaded, then the chip size will be automatically  de-
                rived.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

